#### Concepts

Ah, the building blocks. We have [Austerity](/Austerity), the ever-present specter of scarcity. [Business](/Business) itself, a rather nebulous entity. The inevitable [cycle](/Business_cycle), a recurring nightmare. [Capital](/Capital_(economics)), the elusive prize. [Capital accumulation](/Capital_accumulation), the relentless pursuit. [Capital markets](/Capital_market), where dreams are traded. The ubiquitous [Company](/Company) and its more formidable cousin, the [Corporation](/Corporation). The supposed virtue of [Competition](/Competition_(economics)), often a brutal affair, governed by equally brutal [law](/Competition_law). The very [Definitions](/Definitions_of_capitalism) are a battlefield. Then there's the heavy-handedness of [Economic interventionism](/Economic_interventionism), the seductive whisper of [Economic liberalism](/Economic_liberalism), and the often-painful process of [Economic liberalization](/Economic_liberalization). [Economic surplus](/Economic_surplus), a concept ripe for contention. The driving force of [Entrepreneurship](/Entrepreneurship), often a euphemism for risk-taking with other people’s money. The phantom realm of [Fictitious capital](/Fictitious_capital), the abstract currency of speculation. [Financial market](/Financial_market), a casino for the privileged. The mythical [Invisible hand](/Invisible_hand), contrasted with its more tangible counterpart, the [Visible hand_(economics)](/Visible_hand_(economics)). The fine art of [Marginalism](/Marginalism). The bedrock of [Private property](/Private_property), a concept that has launched a thousand wars. The inevitable march of [Privatization](/Privatization). The ultimate goal, [Profit](/Profit_(economics)), often pursued with a singular, almost pathological, focus. The parasitic practice of [Rent seeking](/Rent_seeking). The delicate dance of [Supply and demand](/Supply_and_demand). The core of Marxist critique, [Surplus value](/Surplus_value). And finally, [Value](/Value_(economics)), a concept as slippery as an eel in oil. Oh, and let's not forget [Wage labour](/Wage_labour), the very engine of much of this critique.

