#### Early Critics

The early dissenters, like [Friedrich Engels](/Friedrich_Engels), were quick to point out the grim realities birthed by the fervor of [industrialization](/Industrial_Revolution) across Europe. Picture this: [14-hour work days](/8-hour_day), the exploitation of [child labor](/Child_labor), and the grim sprawl of [shanty towns](/Shanty_towns). Some modern economists, bless their detached souls, argue that the average person’s living standard saw little to no improvement, or at best, a glacial crawl, before 1840. A rather bleak assessment, wouldn't you agree?

